  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Videolaryngoscopes offer the potential to make tracheal intubation easier for the
      anaesthetist and less traumatic for the patient. This study aims to compare the intubation
      difficulty scores (a validated scoring system for ease of intubation) using the McGrath MAC
      as a videolaryngoscope, the McGrath MAC only as a direct laryngoscope (without video screen)
      and the MacIntosh laryngoscopes.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
